    "recap_headline": "University of Alabama Athletics",
    "recap_text": "TUSCALOOSA, Ala.\n\u2013 The Right Field Terrace at Sewell-Thomas Stadium is open to all fans for Alabama's upcoming weekend series against No. 18 Florida from March 20-22.\nFans of all ages are welcome to sit in the Right Field Terrace area for the Spring Break series. Interested parties can purchase regular game tickets in advance at\nwww.RollTide.com/tickets\n, or on gameday at the Gate 3 (home plate) or Gate 8 (center field) ticket windows at The Joe. Season ticket holders can utilize their ticket for access to the Right Field Terrace, as well.\nAll people wishing to enter the Right Field Terrace with a cooler and/or dog must enter through Gate 6, located directly behind right field. Fans will be expected to follow the same rules as students during their time in the Terrace. A list of the Right Field Terrace rules can be found\nhere\n."
